definitions.definition: Belonging to, or resembling, an abyss ; unfathomable .
definitions.dating_raw: First attested in the mid 17 century.

definitions.definition: Of or belonging to the ocean depths, especially below 2000 metres (6500 ft): abyssal zone .

main_definition: ( archaic ) Belonging to, or resembling, an abyss ; unfathomable . [First attested in the mid 17 century.]
secondary_definitions: ( geography ) Of or belonging to the ocean depths, especially below 2000 metres (6500 ft): abyssal zone . [First attested in the mid 19 century.]
( geology ) Pertaining to or occurring at excessive depths in the earth's crust ; plutonic . [First attested in the late 19 century.]
